<p>EU and world demand for butter and skimmed-milk powder are expected to remain weak. ‘The reactivation of export refunds should support EU exports’, enabling a slight recovery in export levels in 2009, ‘but low demand and strong competition’ will impact on overall exports, with a steady decline in EU exports from 2010 and an acceleration of this decline in 2013, reflecting reduced EU production levels as more milk is directed into higher-value products. Both EU butter production and consumption are projected to decline. </p><p><b>EU: Butter (thousand tonnes) </b></p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
