<p>A similar decline in milk-powder production is expected, with EU production in 2015 being 13.8% below 2007 levels. EU consumption however is projected to recover somewhat, peaking in 2011, some 7.0% above 2007 consumption levels, before falling back to only 6% above 2007 levels. With the exception of an increase in 2011, EU skimmed-milk exports are projected to steadily decline, reaching levels in 2015 that are half the volume exported in 2007.</p><p><b>EU: Skimmed-milk powder (thousand tonnes) </b></p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
