				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>The Dutch-led argument in favour of the quota increase would suggest that EU policy measures in the dairy sector have an impact on trade outcomes. This raises the issue of the trade-distorting nature of these measures, since in the absence of such measures it is held that the EU would lose market share to its competitors. This would appear to raise questions as to the appropriateness of classifying such measures in the ‘green box’ if their trade effects are so marked.</p><p>There are some concerns in the ACP over the trade effects of the reintroduction of EU export refunds, which is leading some governments to look again at the agricultural safeguard provisions included in the interim EPAs. </p>
		</div>
		
